@user1:
`asyncio.sleep` should not be patched directly as this could affect other portions of the code also using this function (other than the one intended to be patched). To avoid this, the object that calls `asyncio.sleep` can have a member function called `_sleep` that it then calls `asyncio.sleep`. Then, the mock will be on the member `_sleep` function.

This goes for any other tests patching `asyncio.sleep` directly.
